# Story scroll effect (KEEP — user approved)

The **home-story** scrollytelling section is the preferred audience/intro pattern for this site. Do not replace or regress it without explicit user request.

## What to preserve

- **Pinned scroll track**: tall track while reading; height driven by right-column content (fallback `calc(var(--story-beats) * 100vh)`)
- **Sticky viewport**: `.home-story` sticks at `top: var(--nav-h)` with video + rail vertically centered
- **Sticky left video**: portrait reel with rounded corners; stays vertically centered in the pinned panel
- **Dashed rail + moving dot**: `.home-story__rail`, dashed `.home-story__line`, `.home-story__dot` driven by `dotProgress` (scrollbar behavior)
- **Article scroll on right only**: all beats stacked in `.home-story__slides-inner`; `translateY` driven by scroll — no crossfade or beat swap
- **Single page scroll**: no nested scroll containers inside the section
- **Large display typography**: `.home-story__copy` / `.home-story__item` use `font-display`, ~`clamp(1.45rem, 2.65vw, 2.15rem)`

## Implementation map

| Piece | Location |
|-------|----------|
| Beats + markup | `pages/index.js` → `STORY_BEATS`, `.home-story-*` |
| Scroll logic | `hooks/useStoryScroll.js` → `useStoryArticleScroll` |
| Hero scroll logic | `pages/index.js` → `useScrollHeroTransition` (inline) |
| Styles | `styles/globals.css` → `.home-story-*`, `.home-story-track--article` |

## Beat sequence (reference)

1. Welcome intro (brand bold + inline links)
2. Situations lead-in
3. Numbered situations 1–3
4. Closing CTA with link
5. Brand personality line

## Static / mobile

Below 901px or `prefers-reduced-motion`: `.home-story-track--static` — all beats stacked, no pin, rail hidden.

## When extending

- Add beats → update `STORY_BEATS` only; track height grows with content
- Do not reintroduce dual scroll (fixed panel + `overflow-y: auto`) or beat-by-beat slide swap on landing
- Services Creative + Technology use the same article-scroll pattern (`pages/services.js`, `.svc-story-track--article`)
- Landing-page-only hero logic stays in `pages/index.js`
